    "body": "Differently from other `fooprg` options, `keywordprg` (used for `K` command) supports an ex command:\r\n```\r\n\tWhen the first character is \":\", the command is invoked as a Vim\r\n\tcommand prefixed with [count].\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be useful to be able to specify (via the Neovim API from Lua, or the Lua API, only) a Lua funcref.\r\n\r\nUse case: setting `keywordprg` to `vim.lsp.buf.hover` (or an appropriate wrapper) to avoid having to remap `K` conditionally.",
